f raw materials re\nmove any atmosphere of mystery from\nthis situation.\nCustoms collections since the first\nof the year have lagged behind those\nof the corresponding period of 1926,\n26th Anniversary\nAnd 26 Years of Good Honest Dentistry Is My Record, and\nI am responsible morally, legally and financially for every piece\nof work done in this office\u2014hence m.v rare in selecting only first-class\nDentists as my associates. If a piece of work is faulty, that patient\nis coming hack indignant\u2014justly so\u2014hence I have the iinpleasantnws\nand double expense of such proceedings, by specifying that the best\nmaterial as well as the best workmanship MUST enter into all dental\nwork leaving this office.\nTR,, K (m T F F uTin\\ rT,ON Then to make prices within\nABSOHTEIA GUARANTEED r\n$lO sls S2O $lO the reach or everyone\nNatural Looking Plate# Our\n.specialty j ns t a ||,\u00bbri labor-saving machinery,\ngold saving dev ices\u2014employed expert dental maehanlcs and gold worker*\nto handle the mechanical work\u2014and leave my skilled operators free to\ndevote all their time to patients.\nI have applied centralized power to tV\ndentistry\u2014but from a democratic rather Fine\nthan an autocratic vlewpoint-and d fr\u00bb\u00ab Brid.s J\nhas made possible better dentistry at Work. Per Tooth.\na vast saving of time and money for and *r. Guaranteed.\n\u2022Ml dental work learlne this office I# snperyis.ri personally by Dr. Frelnt and\nguaranteed. Using only the very latest appliances known to dental selencr, only\nthe latest paln-preventlnr method# used In Ills. FREIOT\u2019S office. glying the least\npossible discomfort.\n\u00abfl YEARS OF GOOD. HONEST PKNISTRY IS (H R RECORD\nA S DR. FREIOT Sgwr\nA ANCE 407\u20147th St. N.W.\u2014407 A N GED\nENTRANCE NEXT TO KAY'S JEWELRY STORE\nGR MU' \\TE AND REGISTERED DENTISTS IN CONSTANT READINESS FOR\nYOUR ATTENTION\nThe entire second floor of two entire buildings given over to operative and me\nchanical dentistry. Everythin* pertaining to the comfort of our patients you\nwill find hpr F V KSS m o\\E OF OUR STRIKING FEATURES\nVERY SPECIAL ATTENTION TO NERVOUS PFOPI.E.\nNo Charge for Extracting When Olher Work Is Being Done\nn a M to P.M. Sundays. 10 A.M. to 1 P.M.\nHonrs. A.M. r< oh Nnm DR. FREIOT and ADDRESS\nBe Sure You Get Into the Right Offlre. Phone Main 10\nbut are far in advance of the corre\nsponding weeks of any other year on\nrecord. The decline is accounted for\nin part by lower prices of imported\ncommodities.\nIncreases In Metals.\nRetail sales in February were 2.5\nper cent greater than in the same\nmonth last year. January also showed\nan increase. Tost office receipts in\nboth January and February marked\nsubstantial Increases. In production,\nthe surveys, while disclosing a de\ncrease in iron and steel, compensate\nhv increases in other metals and in\ntextiles and chemicals.\nForeign markets present increasing\nly sharp competition for American\nexporters, but any loss of business\nwhich may result to the United States\nfrom this situation apparently wfil be\nmore than offset by the improved\neconomic condition of foreign popula\ntion which increases the demand for\nproducts, thereby widening the entire\nmarket.\nPolitical conditions in this country\ncontain nothing that business regards\nas a danger signal, judging from pres\nent activities. Relations between\ncapital and labor, as reflected by the\nnumber of strikes and lockouts, are\nmore cordial than even a year ago.\nWithout attempting to assume the\nroie of infallible prophecy, economists\nIn Wa\u00abhinfton detect nothing *l*rm-\nIn* In the condition of bufttneaa and\nexpect healthy conditions to continue,\nbarring artificial Interruptions which\ncannot he foreseen.\n(Copyrirht. 1P27.)\nENVOYS ARE SHIFTED.\nSeveral District Men Included in\nForeign Service Changes.\nSeveral residents of the District of\nColumbia are involved in recent\nchanges of stations of members of the\nUnited States Foreign Service, Just\nannounced by the State Department.\nRalph A. Boernstein, recently attached\nto the State I>epartment, has been\ndetailed as vice consul at Malmo,\nSweden; Harvey S. Gerry, vice consul\nat Buenos Aires, has been detailed as\ndiplomatic secretary at Asuncion;\nRouts A. Clausel. vice consul at Buenos\nAires, has been detailed as vice consul\nat Kingston. Jamaica, and John L.\nSteward, vice consul at Concepcion,\nhas resigned from the service.\nResignations are announced of\nGranville O. Woodard of California,\nvice consul at Tientsin; Louis G.\nAnciaux of New York, consular agent\nPackard Reduces\n*335\nTHE prices of three of the most popular\nPackard Six models have been reduced\n$335.\nFor example the Packard Six Five-Pas\nger Sedan now costs but $2250 at the factory.\nPackard Washington Motor Car Co.\n0. Coolican, President\nConnecticut at S Potomac Five Thousand\nAt Arequlpa. Peru; Waldo E. Bailey of\nMisalaaippl, vie A consul At Para: Oacar\nF. Brown of Texas, vice consul at\nFrankfort-on-the-Maln; William P.\nHunt of New York, vice consul at\nTientsin; Walter H. Ritsher of Wis\nconsin. vice consul at Reirut. and\nJ. Howard Wetmore of Ohio, vice con\nsul at Dublin.\nHELD TO GRAND JURY.\nSpecial Pinpatch to The Star.\nCLARENDON. Va., March 12.\nRobert F. Brooks, jr.. former assist\nant treasurer of the Clarendon Trust\nCo., recently arrested on four char\u00dfes\nof larceny, was given a preliminary\nhearing before Judge Harry R.\nThomas in Police Court this morn\ning and held for action of the grand\nJury on two of the counts. Involving\n$2,650, which he is alleged he obtained\nfrom W. I.indsay.\nCharges made by Norval Wilson\nSauls and Rose V. Brooks, involving\n$6,000. were dismissed. Brooks was\nrepresented at the hearing by State\nSenator Frank L. Ball; He is at lib\nerty under $5,000 bond.\nHIERARCHY OF FRANCE\nBACKS POPE\u2019S ACTION\nPrelates Defend Vatican for Plac.\nInf Daudet's Newspaper\non Index.\n\nBy the Associated Pros\nROME, March 12.\u2014The Osserva*\ntore Romano, official organ of the\nVatican, ha* puhliahed a collective\ndeclaration by members of the French\nclergy' expressing filial obedience to\nthe Tope in his policy in France,\nwhere he recently placed\ndefs royalist newspaper. L\u2019Actlon\nFrancatse. on the Index on account\nof its declarations regarding the\nVatican.\nThe declaration by the French\nclergy bears the signatures of 5\ncardinals, 20 archbishops and P 2\nbishops. The document asserts that\nthe attitude of the Pope has not been\nmotivated by politics.\nIt declares the Pope did not wish\nto Interfere with the question of\nmonarchism in Fra nee.","height":"27288","width":"20835"}}
